@startuml grace-gap-problem
' Standard UML theme (default colours/shapes).
skinparam dpi 300
title The grace gap: a fixed grace period can cut off an unfinished handoff

participant "Deployment\ncontroller" as Dep
participant "kubelet" as Kubelet
participant "terminating pod\n(400 stateful procs)" as P2
participant "Phoenix\nEndpoint" as EP
participant "Horde" as Horde
participant "surviving\nnode" as Surv
actor Client

Dep -> Kubelet: rolling update -> terminate pod
Kubelet -> P2: SIGTERM
note right of Kubelet: terminationGracePeriodSeconds = 30
P2 -> P2: trap SIGTERM
P2 -> EP: drain (stop accepting)
P2 -> Horde: hand off 400 stateful processes

loop each process (serialize + transfer CRDT state)
  Horde -> Surv: transfer state
end
note over Horde,Surv: handoff takes ~45s under load

Kubelet -> P2: SIGKILL (at t = 30s)
note over P2: ~150 processes not yet moved\ndie with unsynced state

Client -> Surv: reconnect
Surv --> Client: state missing recent updates
@enduml
